Section 1:
1 L.D. 78
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 EDUCATION AND CULTURAL AFFAIRS
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 42, L.D. 78, “An Act to Require
10 Elementary School Students to Learn Cursive Writing”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, Directing the Department of Education to Collect Data on Cursive
13 Instruction in Maine Public Schools'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
15 'Sec. 1. Department of Education to collect data on cursive instruction.
16 Resolved: That the Department of Education, within existing resources, shall conduct a
17 survey of school administrative units to determine the number of elementary and middle
18 schools in the State that offer instruction on cursive handwriting, the number of elementary
19 and middle schools in the State that do not offer instruction on cursive handwriting and for
20 which grade levels cursive handwriting instruction is offered.
21 Sec. 2. Report. Resolved: That, by January 15, 2026, the Department of Education
22 shall submit a report based on the results of the survey conducted pursuant to section 1 to
23 the Joint Standing Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs. The committee is
24 authorized to submit legislation related to the report to the Second Regular Session of the
25 132nd Legislature.'
26 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
27 number to read consecutively.
28 SUMMARY
2299 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve that directs the Department of
3300 Education to conduct a survey of school administrative units to determine the number of
3311 elementary and middle schools in the State that offer instruction on cursive handwriting,
3322 the number of elementary and middle schools in the State that do not offer instruction on
3333 cursive handwriting and for which grade levels cursive handwriting instruction is offered.
Page 1 - 132LR0324(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 42, L.D. 78
314 The department must submit a report based on the results of the survey to the Joint Standing
325 Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs by January 15, 2026.
336 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
347 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR0324(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
